# One Place for One Kind of Action

When "doing X" is a repeated concept (e.g. "add a failure to the report"),
give it **one** method or function. All call sites use that entry point.

Example: `_add` in `Failure` is the only way to append a `Failed` record. The
construction of `Failed` and the check "not already in list" live there. No
ad-hoc `Failed(...); self.append(...)` elsewhere. The reader knows where to
look to understand "how we add a failure," and the behavior stays consistent.

Same for "create Parent from string" — one function; "create Parent from file"
calls it or shares the same construction path. One kind of action, one home.
